\subsection{Minimal Example}
The following code snippet illustrates the use of the \themename
theme in a very simple Beamer presentation.

\begin{lstlisting}
\documentclass{beamer}
\usetheme{smds}       % Use SMDS theme
\title{Hello World}
\date{\today}
\author{Adrian Rumpold}
\institute{University of Augsburg}
\begin{document}
  \maketitle
  \section{Introduction}
  \begin{frame}{Agenda}
    \begin{itemize}
    \item Eat ice cream.
    \item Drink coffee.
    \end{itemize}
  \end{frame}
\end{document}
\end{lstlisting}

\subsection{Dependencies}

\themename depends on the |beamer| class and the following standard packages:
\begin{multicols}{3}
  \begin{itemize}
    \item |tikz|
