  \begin{itemize}
    \item |roboto|
    \item |droidmono|
  \end{itemize}
\end{multicols}

\section{Customizing}
\subsection{Section title pages}

The \themename theme provides multiple options for section and subsecution title pages.

These options can be customized when loading the theme:
\begin{lstlisting}
\usetheme[
  sectionpage=<...>,
  subsectionpage=<...>
]{smds}
\end{lstlisting}

\subsubsection{Options for \texttt{sectionpage}}
\begin{description}
\item[none] (default) Do not insert a title page before a new |\section|
\item[simple] Add a title page with the section title before a new |\section|
\item[agenda] Add an agenda overview page with the next section highlighted before a new |\section|
\end{description}

\subsubsection{Options for \texttt{subsectionpage}}
\begin{description}
\item[none] (default) Do not insert a title page before a new |\subsection|
\item[simple] Add a title page with the section and subsection title before a new |\subsection|
\item[agenda] Add an agenda overview page with the next subsection highlighted before a new |\subsection|
\end{description}

\subsection{Debug options}

The \themename theme supports the |grid| switch, which renders a rectangular grid
in the background of every frame in the presentation and can be used to aid the positioning
of elements on the page.

To use this feature, simply specify the parameter when loading the theme:
\begin{lstlisting}
  \usetheme[
    grid=on,
    % ... other options
  ]{smds}
  \end{lstlisting}

